{
  "texts": [
    "The multi-task loss L of Fast R-CNN is jointly expressed with the two output layers, specifically training for classification and bounding box regression for each labeled ROI.",
    "For the trained model, the discrete probability distribution p, computed by a softmax over K + 1 categories per ROI from a fully connected layer, is defined by",
    "the output bounding box regression offset is given by",
    "Where K is the object class indexed by k. The Iverson bracket indicator function [u ≥ 1] is employed to omit all background RoIs (Girshick et al., 2014b).",
    "in which L cls (p, u) is log loss for true class u."
  ]
}